<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>schizo.land</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
    <script src="/script.js"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <h3>schizo.land</h3>
    <form action="/submit-post" method="post" id="post-form">
        <fieldset>
            <legend>write a post. if it is approved, it will show up later.</legend>
            <textarea name="body"></textarea><br>
            <input type="submit" value="Submit post for review">
        </fieldset>
    </form>
    <p>
        you can avoid requiring approval by registering an account.
        if you make enough approved posts, you can be made trusted.
        this privilege can be revoked, however.
        an account will also allow you to (optionally) have a username.
    </p>
    <form action="/register-user" method="post" id="register-form">
        <fieldset>
            <legend>user registration</legend>
            <label for="register-username">username:</label>
            <input type="text" name="username" id="register-username" size="16"><br>
            <label for="register-password">password:</label>
            <input type="password" name="password" id="register-password"><br>
            <label for="register-password-confirmation">password (again):</label>
            <input type="password" name="password_confirmation" id="register-password-confirmation"><br>
            <input type="submit" value="Register account">
        </fieldset>
    </form>
    <p>if you already have an account, log in:</p>
    <form action="/authenticate-user" method="post" id="login-form">
        <fieldset>
            <legend>user login</legend>
            <label for="login-username">username:</label>
            <input type="text" name="username" id="login-username" size="16"><br>
            <label for="login-password">password:</label>
            <input type="password" name="password" id="login-password"><br>
            <input type="submit" value="Log in">
        </fieldset>
    </form>
    <p>here are the last 100 approved posts:</p>
</body>

</html>